fields: Ok, sure. I just woke up.
We'll talk things over with them early next week, okay?
Okay. I saw a young girl out in the garden. Is she Haruko's?
At 79, he lived a good, long life, right?
That girl is Grandpa's illegitimate child.
He never said a word about it. And we don't even know where his lover is.
Sheesh, I can't decide if it's embarrassing or just shameful.
You really did die peacefully, didn't you, Grandpa?
It doesn't matter. Any amount will help.
Really, any amount will help. Though recently, sutra recitations and the giving of a posthumous name have become quite expensive.
Good to see you all after so long.
Daikichi, it's sure been a while.
So busy you can't visit your own mother? You weren't even here for New Year's. Here. Wait, Reina!
But is it really true? I know my older brother felt lonely living alone, but...
Still, how could a 79 year-old man do this?
Well, regardless of whether he could have done it or not, you've gotta hand it to him.
Hey, wanna trade? Wait! Just leave it like that.
Very! You sure are good at cat's cradle, Reina-chan.
Here, Reina-chan, let me show you.
Daikichi said he'll watch it. Come on now.
Everyone, please offer your final farewells.
Grandpa will love this flower the most.
She can talk! And she's not a pain!
No, she can't talk! It's so boring being with her!
Here, take all of these and go away.
I can't. I'm at the store all day.
I would if she was a more proper girl.
Mom. You're always at home. Couldn't you watch her for a bit?
Don't you know how much I've had to sacrifice over the years?
We're not even sure that she's really Grandpa's child.
Anyway, I say we try putting her in a care facility as soon as possible.
Daikichi, get me a green one.
What size are you? I don't know.
Don't you want some skirts too?
These are all pants. They don't allow skirts at the daycare.
Well, daycares don't just let kids in that easily.
Rin-chan! Stop it, Reina! This is important. Rin-chan!
Just hold on, I'm almost done!
Listen, the daycare we're going to today is only a temporary one.
Put me down! Put me down!
Embarrassed that the other kids might see me carrying you?
I can't say I'll be back before it gets dark, but I'll get here as fast as I can.
I'm off. Wait for me, Rin.
I brought my own. I have to leave a little early today.
Oh, really? Alright then, see you.
Take a picture of this sample. Okay.
Kawachi-san, there's a caller on line four asking about the private audience.
Rin-chan, don't bring it down, okay? Okay.
Yes, this is Kawachi. We appreciate your business.
Yes, I'll be able to leave in just a bit. I'm sorry.
Kawachi-san, I need you to sign!
Kawachi, you shipped this out yesterday, right?
I get it. Way to go.
Daikichi, don't let the moon catch us!
By the way, when did you start sleeping on that side?
Those of you with Type B, listen carefully. Should this be left alone, it will surely threaten the fabric of your life!
Turn it off! Turn off that sick show!
Do you have a girlfriend, Kawachi-san? What?
You've been rushing home early lately. No, I don't have one.
But, if you keep this up...
Those sales figures weren't born out of willpower or determination.
It was just a coincidence. My name means "super lucky," after all.
In fact, he was just stacking the pressure on me. I think I'm going bald from the stress.
So, Gotou-san, do you really have a kid?
Don't judge me just because I'm short!
I can carry them. It's fine, I got it.
It looks like it really upsets her.
But since they can't sweat much during autumn and winter, they have to pee a lot more to compensate.
Make sure you pee before going to bed.
I wish I could ask her some things.
Men shouldn't give in so easily! Do your best!
Rin, I'll make dinner right away.
So, how's it going? I'm doing fine.
Hold on, I thought you didn't want to get involved with her?
I'm gonna try to find Rin's mom this weekend, so I'll be on your side of town.
Make sure you dress her properly for the cold!
Our two kids seem to get along well.
It's good to see you, Rin-chan!
Don't complain if you get hungry again.
I'm sorry I didn't finish my plate.
Now then, on to tomorrow's forecast.
She even acted like going on the train was some kind of trip.
He's right. You two were like that too.
See! You used to be exactly like her!
You don't look old enough to be my grandma!
Huh? Did I make a mistake?
You hang it on your pinky. Like this?
What on earth is going on in here?!
These are pretty! What are they called? Beanbags.
Yeah, maybe. Having a mother is important, after all.
They're Kazumi's. Did you say Kazumi?
It sure brings back memories. Any luck at Grandpa's house?
I see. Still, I think it's best not to rush  to press the issue with Rin-chan.
I'm not sure whether we ever told you or not, but your mother started working after you were born.
Will you be okay? Do you want Dad to take you?
I just thought it'd be nice to have a grandchild! I'd take care of it!
That's when women get left behind! Besides, I still want to fit into a swimsuit and go out drinking!
Did Grandpa use one? No, the maid did.
You said it. It sure keeps us busy.
Gotou-san, have you ever thought you sacrificed a lot to raise your child?
Like when I asked to be demoted?
Even if I have sacrificed myself, it's not something I'd want to talk about.
You know, like the soul of language.
No, I completely understand what you mean!
Kawachi-kun, your child's older than mine!
But it's just sweat! I don't care if it's sweat or not.
Did you have a scary dream?
Everything will be fine until you're a young lady.
I mean, everything will be fine until you're a grown-up woman!
But the bathroom's scary! Then I'll go with you at night.
And even if you still wet the bed, all we have to do is change your pants.
You won't be mad? I won't be mad. Nor will I laugh about it.
I'm really sorry for suddenly bringing this up, Hidaka-san.
I know this is really unexpected, but could you please transfer me to a section with no overtime?
But, I have a child as well.
I'll try to convince the section head to grant your request.
I'm truly sorry. Thank you for understanding.
Still, your subordinates won't be too happy.
Why do you have to do it, Kawachi-san?!
Can't you ask one of your relatives?
I don't want to work for someone other than you!
Look, I know this is really sudden, but managers and the like transfer suddenly all the time!
Towel, lunch box, slippers, toothbrush, cup... With your name on them all.
Futon?! Oh, that's only for babies.
Huh? Rin-chan, you say a lot of weird things.
Is it just you and your mom?
It's when you stop being married. I wonder if my mom's gone because she got divorced. Who knows.
See you soon, Rin-chan. Goodbye! What do you want for dinner?
He's not very sociable, so he has a hard time making friends.
Thank you so much. Oh, no! I should be saying that.
Kouki-kun said he doesn't have a dad.
Do you want to meet her?
Have you ever heard anything about his maid?
Thank you. But I really can't go out at night.
You said it. I have to go to the daycare after all.
She's real scary when she gets angry.
But they've spent so much time preparing for it, so why not bring your kid along?
Are you saying you want to go out drinking sometimes?
So, do you know her name?
How could she abandon such a cute girl?
Thank you! Here, Rin-chan. Is orange juice alright?
Rin might fall asleep on our way home.
Fine, fine. I'm going to the bathroom.
Our sales are in a slump this month. Even if we sell a decent amount, upper management will only see last year's records.
Wasn't Yuu-kun really cute? You love little kids, don't you?
Yup! Here's the mail. Oh, thanks.
I didn't even ask for this!
Are you sure?! I'm sure, I'm sure!

Since the children's name tags can be flipped around, their names should remain unseen on their way to and from school. Also, your children should not go alone to places like the park. And even if they know someone, they should never go with them.
How do we find out what immunizations they've gotten so far?
Sorry, looks like I just asked a really stupid question. Don't worry.
Do you have Rin-chan's child care handbook?
Then you'll find out. Oh, okay.
What's up? I jumped over your shadow!
Put me down! Put me down! Put me down, now!
Yeah, thanks. She's almost got everything she needs.
All of the brand label and fashionable ones are already sold out! I'll just get a regular one.
I mean, you transferred sections, right?
If Masako found this, she would probably dispose of it,
which is why I have chosen this discreet method.
By now, this old fool's drained of energy,
which is why I'm giving up writing this blog.
Mii-chan said I wasn't cute at all.
Twinkle, twinkle, little star... Umm, Rin? What are you doing?
You were just dreaming. There's nothing to be afraid of.
They have ones for kids! Really?
Umm, you are Yoshii Masako-san, right?
I want to meet you in person to discuss some things.
Sorry, but I have no idea where you live.
Once you're a little older, I'll show you how to do it.
I guess I'll decide after I meet her.
Watch over Rin for a bit.
No, there's someone else coming. Non-smoking, please.
My stress just keeps piling up! I know what you mean.
Isn't that a bit much? No, I think it'll be just perfect.
Mama, I have to pee! Okay, just hold on.
I'm sorry, you just look so much like him.
Still, I think Souichi-san seemed more kind. Yeah.
Wow, she's like a young lady!
It's my pen name. Sorry, I'm a total mess after staying up all night working to meet my deadline.
Umm, my work was the reason. But I was also Souichi-san's maid.
That's why, even though I kept telling myself I wasn't going to be her mother, I gave it my all to work and raise her at the same time.
I heard that Rin used to stay with you in your apartment at night.
Did you go out sometimes at night then?
Didn't you ever consider how she felt when no one was beside her when she woke up?
How else was I supposed to raise her by myself?
Didn't my grandfather want the three of you to live as a family?
I'm not her mother anymore. I can't decide for her.
Is she dear to you or not?
If she has a different surname than her guardian's, she might get picked on.
Could you promise me this one thing?
As a woman, I don't really have any attachment to my surname.
I'm only thinking of what's best for Rin.
Besides, it's cruel for us to decide for her.
She sounds like a bad egg to me.
How could anyone abandon such a cute girl?
What are you talking about?! All mothers worry about their children!
It's natural that a child should have the same surname as their guardian's.
Okay, I get that, but how do I explain that to Rin?
She already has a real name.
Well, since she's a girl, her surname will change anyway once she gets married.
Things can be tough, even in elementary school. I'm positive.
Don't bring up something like that so carelessly!
I'm not being careless! We have to decide one way or another, right?!
It does matter! No, it doesn't!
I'm not going to let Rin be passed around again.
Promise me that and the knife is yours. Okay!
Umm, do I push or pull?
Don't drink the water in here. Okay.
Hey, Rin... I'm not your dad.
Listen. This is only if you're up for it, but, how should I put it... Would you...
Also, your name would change to "Kawachi Rin."
I like it because it's the same name as Grandpa's.
This'll always be your home, you know.
What? Why? I'm not really sure.
I'm sorry! I should have held you back then!
I'll hold you the next time you cry!
Go on! She'll grow up in the blink of an eye.
Rin! How many times do I have to tell you not to leave my side like that?!
You're a young lady now, so start acting like one!
Have you ever had cereal before? Nope.
No, I don't mind buying it. But you normally have that for breakfast.
Well, let's see... It looks like candy, but you can have it as a meal.
Commemorate? It's like creating a memory.
At home? At my parents' home.
When I offered to trade, she would just scream and say she didn't want hand-me-downs.
A plum tree? Yeah, a plum tree!
No plum tree? Well, a tree doesn't grow as fast as a morning glory.
It's like they say, "Good things will come to those who wait." "So don't be impatient!"
You're a spitting image of Grandpa, you know.
Yeah, Kouki-kun says he's going to become one.
Why don't you try that with your plum tree?
How tall does a plum tree grow?
A fire? I think it's the police.
If a stranger tries to talk to you, blow really hard into the whistle, okay?
That's dog food! It's made for dogs.
My rice balls are still number one though! They sure are good.
Oh, that's okay. It's no problem.
Now your knapsack's got marks all over it.
You used that stick to scrape home walls, didn't you?
Can you read my mind?! I knew it right away!
Kouki-kun, you shouldn't blow it when nothing's wrong!
Kouki-kun, hurry up! It's not a shortcut otherwise!
Hey, that plum tree is because I'm starting school, right?
Souichi-san was the one who planted it.
What kind is it? A small one.
Wrong! It rises in the east!
I have some work to do, so I'll be leaving.
And even if he didn't, we'll just plant a new one to celebrate your entrance into school. A six year old tree.
That's right. Good job! Daikichi told me.
Grandpa planted it when I was born.
So, you have the same kind of tree as Kazumi?
It really is. Daikichi, we'll miss the train! Coming!
See you. I'll walk you to the station.
There's a weird old man outside!
Please, it was extremely rude of us.
Can we come in? Yeah! Sure.
No, we just came to see you! Oh, okay. Umm...
Reina-chan, do you like sweet buns? What are they?
They're round sweets. Okay, I like them!
We don't know what's going to happen tomorrow.
Well, it's probably tough living with your in-laws, right?

What did you tell them? I took care of it. I left them a letter, though I didn't say where we were going. And I'll take Reina to school. I haven't given much thought beyond that. I haven't even told my parents yet.
This is my cousin, Haruko, from my mother's side!
I got a vegetable sponge cake!
Umm, I guess she's sort of pretty for a mom.
Who cares how old she is?
We normally have to eat whatever my mother-in-law wants.
Mama, can we have this at home too?
It's good! Thank you, Rin-chan! Reina, hold your chopsticks properly.
A bra! Stop that, Reina! Don't pull on it!
Oh, good point. So I've really gained weight?!
No, I didn't mean you. I mean in general for people over thirty.
I wouldn't mind being thirty again. Life's just not the same when you get older, is it?
Don't do weird things like that, Dai-chan!
I didn't even give them my address.
Even though they're married? Yeah. I always pretend I'm sleeping when they fight. Give me your hand. Okay.
Don't be ridiculous! We always cook together!
Reina, you've got some rice on your face.
Who is that? Rin-chan! It's Kouki-kun.
Mama, you're better off single, right?
Daikichi, can I have a rice ball?
It'd be rude of me to pry into their business.
Reina, didn't I tell you to hurry up and finish? Haruko?
Good morning! Reina-chan, did you come with your mom today? Yup, I did! We ran away from home secretly, so we had to take the train today!
I told you to hold on to it tightly!
Yeah. My husband's at home with our son. How's Yuu-kun doing?
It's good to hear that your husband's helping out though.
This is the first time! His business trip was rescheduled.
Haruko, I'm not saying you will, but you're not planning on taking this any further, are you?
Sheesh, I guess I was worrying over nothing.
But, I'm not being very realistic.
I guess in the end I'm better off where I am now.
I guess it was inevitable, wasn't it? That's the only way I can watch over Reina.
He works overtime a lot, and we never really talk anyway.
I don't want to feel like an old woman.
What's wrong? It's your turn, Reina.
I'm so sorry. Haruko must have troubled you a lot.
Come by again whenever you feel like it.
Mama, Mama! Does that mean we can come back on Sunday?
Okay! It looks so good on you! Let's go.
I'm fine. I mean, if I sleep now, I'm done for.
If you need me, just call my cell.
You've got ink on your face again. Yeah?
Shall we make your lunch? Yeah.
Although Grandpa would be happy if you brought your own flowers for him. Right? That's what I thought!
What is it? I'll be right back!
I've got a lot in here.
Wait, then that makes me your mom's sister.
What is it? Why are you here?
That all might take some time though.
Not really. Were you feeling lonely?
Although I don't know what he'll be like in another fifty years.
Just the backyard, okay? Okay! I'll lead the way!
If I... If I don't forget all those things... I'll...
He knew they were Grandpa's favorite.
That will always be Grandpa's grave, won't it?
Saionji-sensei, could you look over it one last time?
I know! Wait for me! It's hard to run in these shoes!

Typhoon No. 13 continues to exhibit strong signs of force as it makes its way up north. It struck the Southern Daitou Islands at 11:00 PM last night. So far there have been no reports on how this will affect transportation.
As the typhoon alters its route towards the east, it is expected to make landfall in the Toukai region this evening.
Sensei, how much space should we leave?
Next, all the first graders will have art class. Gather in front of each of your morning glories. Understood?
What's that? It's my kids' educational endowment insurance.
I can't wait until they're older to get insurance.
Money's tight since we have two kids.
We may not be full-time employees here, but it's nice they give us a welfare pension and health insurance.
You guys really seem like dads.
Bring something when I tell you to bring it! Run and go get it!
Kouki-san. We're having art class now. Your morning glories look great, Kouki-san!
Do you like drawing? Sort of, I guess.
No, he won't! We went to the same daycare.
It's pretty windy out there, isn't it?
You see the storm? Yup, it's wild outside.
I'll let you speak to her as well to confirm.
Now I'm crying! Where are you going?
Rin-chan, the eggs are done boiling! Please peel them! Okay!
Kouki, do you love your mom?
Food really does taste better when we're all together!
Don't worry about the rest, I'll finish them later.
I was never able to give him this kind of chance.
I wanted to open up the storm shutters.
We're leaving! Kouki-kun, we're gonna be late.
I bet you could become a manga artist! What? No way!
Sayaka-chan's dad is the same age as you Daikichi, thirty-one. Really?!
Sorry, but if you don't mind, could you tell me your company's name?
Oh, that must be me! I'm indebted to your company!
I'm a manager at my agency now.
He was in school with me. We're both from the neighborhood.
He's the same age as us. Really? Nice to meet you.
It got cold all of sudden, didn't it?
Umm, all the kids are in the gym already.
And then my kid got the flu last week.
I actually understood where those mothers were coming from, which makes me feel even more down.
Daikichi, I'm getting my knapsack, so wait here!
And don't run in the hallways! Okay!
Kouki's teeth are already growing in, right?
I would wear the bare minimum.
Did you really do all of that, Daikichi-san?
What are you doing? Walk with Kouki. No!
She doesn't have the flu, but still...
She fell asleep just before you came.
I know I was supposed to at least give her a sports drink, but she won't drink or eat anything.
When a child is in really bad shape, they need someone to stick by their side.
Your stomach won't like it if you have all of it at once.
You'll feel much better once you get some sleep.
I'll make you some yummy rice porridge now, okay?
Now, put this in the pot. Okay.
You'll like it. Kouki eats it too when he's sick.
Can I come home with you guys?
Get some bread and a drink for breakfast tomorrow.
Do you wanna get something too? Maybe some cereal?
Did I pass it on to her?
Yeah. I'm making that rice porridge again.
Nitani-san, you might have caught Rin's cold while taking care of her.
He can't do it well just yet.
She just lost one of her upper teeth.
You didn't know parents keep their kid's baby teeth in cases for memories?
Thank you. But isn't that Kouki's?
Rin, count me in for jump-roping too!
I could use the exercise. Us too.
Why do you get to be the only one who looks cool?!
Although, adults are really something too.
I could've jumped more the normal way though!
How much longer? About ten minutes.
I bet my parents will be shocked to see how much you've grown.
Rin-chan, we've been waiting for you!
It's not like she can't walk ten minutes.
They used to be yours, right? Yeah.
Why didn't you help her out?! Her gums are really red!
Mom told me you're getting married. Is that true? Yeah.
You should talk to him about it then.
You'd have no other choice anyway.
I don't think there's anything really special about being a parent.
My adult teeth are growing in.
Oh, Daikichi? That was quick. You can put your bags in Grandpa's room.
His lover? He was 79, you know!
So that girl is your sister?
You're 30 years old! You know better than to make jokes like that!
I know that, but isn't there some usual amount people give?
Oh, Dai-chan, it's good to see you. Mama!
I've got you now! Now be a good girl and stay quiet. No, I don't want to! What is it? Nothing.
You just look a lot like Grandpa when he was young.
He left behind a child care book. It says her name is Rin.
Daikichi, would you bring the cushions from the closet, please?
Go ahead and get some sleep.
Watch over my older brother, please.
No! I want to make a flower garden! I want to!
I don't know what the point in trying to find someone who left their child and ran away is.
She has no sense of responsibility.
My brother was also really stubborn about it.
It's such a pain! She hasn't even lost her baby teeth!
It's like you own a candy shop! Sorry about that, Dai-chan.
Later on is one thing, but who's going to watch over that girl right now?
Not to mention she has a hard time talking.
I'm not as free as you think! Besides, do you have any idea how hard it is to raise a child?
I'd feel bad for the girl if she was looked after half-heartedly.
It's not like you have any intention of taking her in, do you, Brother? Be realistic.
There's nothing left to fill it with.
Rin, don't just leave my side like that! You scared me!
It's dangerous if we don't hold hands.
Where should I measure it from? I don't know.
Just hang on, we're almost there. Okay.
Could you get that? Hello, Maeda residence. Oh, I'm so sorry to hear about your family's loss. Yes, just a moment.
Haruko? Sorry, I didn't have your cell phone number.
Say, how do I enter a kid into a daycare?
So you really did take Rin-chan home?!
For the time being. What do you mean?
The thing is, I can't take tomorrow off. What's the proper protocol here?
Couldn't you do something? I'm not sure what I could do. I guess for now you could ask at city hall.
Nothing, it's on my end. Mama, is that Rin-chan? Are you okay?
I'm tired of waiting! Haruko-san, the miso soup is about done.
It sounds like you're busy. I'll call later - Rin-chan!
Man, there's so few of them!
So about the daycare we're going to today...
You shouldn't have your elbow on the table when you eat!
Temporary? It means you'll be there until we find a place that'll let you officially enter.
I'll leave her with you then. Okay, see you later!
If I lie, I'll swallow a thousand needles.
You're going all out, right from the start of the month, huh?
You're late! Sorry, sorry. Go change.
Yes, please wait a moment. Kawachi-san. It's Miyata-san from Mitsutomo Commerce.
It's unusual for you to mess up. Forgive me.
I already apologized to the customer.
Let's go for a drink later. It has been a while.
I said it's sweat! I'm saying it's sweat too!
What do you mean? You're only six years old.
You used to always take the last train of the day. Our sales were out of this world last year, thanks to you.
Oh, thank you. Fourth floor, right?
It's not easy surpassing your own record, is it?
No, it's just you're so thin, I was wondering if you really had a baby.
I wish she was still in sales.
She's been wetting the bed recently.
Maybe it's psychological. Still, kids really do sweat an astonishing amount.
Oh yeah, I remember hearing that as a kid.
Her mother must have had a good reason to leave her.
I guess having a mother is really important, isn't it?
I read picture books and had staring contests...
I wasn't asking about you. Oh, she's fine too.
I have to get involved. You're watching over her, after all.
Okay. Call me when you're at the station.
I'm sorry, I don't have anything a child would like.
She likes things adults do anyway. Isn't that right?
What a drag! What's with that family?!
Brother, you really took this girl in?!
It will be warm and sunny across the nation today.
Temperatures will be about two degrees higher than usual for this time of year. I'm just going to the bathroom.
I can't go if you're right outside.
No, she's actually pretty chatty at home.
But, all the adults here last time were really tense around her.
Idiot. If adults are in a bad mood, kids think they're angry at them.
But Rin's smarter than you were!
Rin-chan, you like cat's cradle, don't you?
Now watch your Auntie do it, okay?
I think you mean "Grandma," don't you?
Oh my! What a nice girl!
Did you want to do a four-step ladder? Wow!
Did you make this? Yes, I knitted it from thin wool.
Its weight balance is much better than simply making loops out of the wool.
Hold on! Since she's good with her hands, maybe she can play with beanbags!
Thanks for coming. Not at all.
You're really doing great, raising a child and working at the same time.
My husband doesn't help out at home at all.
Are you heading over to Grandpa's house?
Yeah, I figured I might find something there about Rin's mom.
I got it done the same as Reina-chan!
